29/06/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Interior Minister Georgi Petkanov and his Turkish counterpart, Abdulkadir Aksu, met on Saturday (28 June) to discuss a trilateral agreement with Iran on joint efforts against drug trafficking. Petkanov called the joint effort appropriate, since the Balkan drug route passes through all three countries. Bilateral agreements already exist between Turkey and Bulgaria and between Turkey and Iran.
In other news, Bulgaria and Turkey broke ground Saturday on a new border checkpoint near the town of Malko Turnovo in southern Bulgaria. Construction is to completed by year's end, at a cost of 1m euros. (Trud, 24 Chassa - 29/06/03; BTA, Anadolu Agency - 28/06/03)
